attacks on two U.S. embassies in East Africa only minutes apart
Friday probably were carried out by one of a small number of
sophisticated terrorist groups presumed to have attacked U.S.
installations in the past. By Philip Shenon.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-SCENE (Nairobi) _ Floodlights lit the 60-foot-high pile
of rubble and metal that once was a three-story building, while Red
Cross workers and soldiers crawled over it like ants, hammering
feverishly with picks and shovels and stopping only once in a while
to listen for signs of life: a muffled voice, a whimper or a cry.
By James C. McKinley Jr.
</P>
