   AFRICA-SECURITY (Washington) _ The two bombed embassies did not
meet the security standards set for the State Department's overseas
posts by an independent review panel created following terrorist
attacks against the American embassy and marine barrack in Beirut.
The embassies had never been modified because the White House and
Congress had never provided enough money, officials said. By James
Risen.
