<P>
   NEVIS-SECEDE _ ST. KITTS, U.S. Virgin Islands _ Imagine a
country of less than 10,000 people, where almost every family's
supported by the Four Seasons Resort, the biggest employer. That's
what will be created if residents on the tiny Caribbean island of
Nevis vote Aug. 10 to secede from their union with St. Kitts. For
years, Nevis residents have complained that St. Kitts dominates the
federation of St. Kitts-Nevis's resources and has tried to take
control of Nevis's thriving offshore financial industry. Now Nevis
has a chance to break free. If secession passes, Nevis will become
the smallest country in the Western Hemisphere. (Emling, Cox News
Service). MOVED
</P>
