<P>
   VINEYARD _ EDGARTOWN, Mass. _ If you live on the fashionable
summer resort of Martha's Vineyard, what do you do when President
Clinton comes to vacation? The answer for may residents is to get
off the island, in order to cash in on the extra demand for lodging
or to avoid the crush of media and the curious. Those who stay
describe the hassles and the benefits of hosting the First Tourist.
(Dart, Cox News Service).
</P>
