A4326 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      08-08 0178
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Aug. 9 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
Stew Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   BLUE-WHALES (Los Angeles) _ For unknown reasons, the blue whale,
the largest mammal in the world, has been heading to California
waters in increasing numbers during the past few years. By Brooke
Olson. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.) &QL; 
. &QL; 
JJ-WHALE (Los Angeles) _ Sea World and its biologist have given up
looking. The Coast Guard hasn't been looking. The media has turned
its attentions elsewhere. But the search for JJ, the rehabilitated
orphan whale, is still hot news on whale watching vessels up and
down the California coast. ``Missing'' photos of JJ hang in Captain
Don's boat as he heads out from Santa Barbara's Stearns Wharf each
day. By Brooke Olson. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
