<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-STERN-BEARD-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOME STUBBLE AT NBA TALKS 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ David Stern, the commissioner of the National
Basketball Association, appeared at the bargaining session between
the league and the players union last Thursday with something new:
a beard in progress.
</P>
<P>
   Afterward, during a telephone conference call, Stern was asked
about the beard. Did it have some significance, perhaps relating to
the negotiations?
</P>
<P>
   ``The betting,'' he responded, ``is whether I should shave
before we make a deal. But frankly I only want it to be a
summertime thing, and it might have to go to winter if that was the
case and I don't want to do that.''
</P>
<P>
   The question and answer were the last in a series of questions
and answers that went on for about 30 minutes. The NBA later posted
a transcript of the conference call on its Internet site (NBA.com).
But the question about the beard and Stern's answer were omitted.
The transcript was also accompanied by Stern's picture. It was
obviously an outdated photo: it showed a clean-shaven commissioner.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
