<P>
   CLINTON-LAWYERS _ WASHINGTON _ In the run-up to his Aug. 17
grand jury testimony, President Clinton is being advised by a
battery of attorneys who are mining a sophisticated series of
back-channel, yet perfectly legal, contacts who keep the apprised
of what independent counsel Kenneth Starr is learning from his
investigation. The system isn't foolproof, but it helps keep
Clinton from flying blind into his date with Starr. (Deans, Cox
News Service 900).
</P>
<P>
   DECADE _ WASHINGTON _ Let's take a stroll through the graveyard
of decades. There's the gaudy 1920s marker, with its epitaph of
``Roaring.'' Keep on marching past the ``swinging'' '60s headstone
and the human-shaped ``Me Decade'' of the '70s. The monstrous
tombstone for the '80s can't be missed _ it denotes the ``Greed
Decade.'' But now is a particularly grave time in pop culture land.
Just 17 months shy of 2000, there's no consensus among trend
trackers, pop culture mavens and futurists on a catch phrase for
the '90s. (Abulhassan, Cox News Service 650).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (l) lifestyle categories.
</P>
