<HEADLINE>
NEWS MEDIA AND THE MCIVER STORY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JIM REEVES 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dale Hansen, the Dallas-Fort Worth WFAA/Channel 8 sports anchor
whose reporters took the early lead in advancing the real story
behind the Everett McIver situation in Wichita Falls, is missing
the point when he says on the radio that the local papers haven't
been as aggressive in handling the story because they're running
scared of the Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's an attitude among the media that `We don't want to
take on the Cowboys, we certainly don't want to take on MichcEX
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
